{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/referrerPolicy","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement\"><code>HTMLLinkElement</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/as\"><code>as</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/fetchPriority\"><code>fetchPriority</code></a></li><li><em><code>referrerPolicy</code></em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/rel\"><code>rel</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/relList\"><code>relList</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLElement\"><code>HTMLElement</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element\"><code>Element</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Node\"><code>Node</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The\n  <strong><code>HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy</code></strong>\n  property reflect the HTML <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/link#attr-referrerpolicy\"><code>referrerpolicy</code></a> attribute of the\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/link\"><code>&lt;link&gt;</code></a> element defining which referrer is sent when fetching the\n  resource.\n</p>\n<p>See the HTTP <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Referrer-Policy\"><code>Referrer-Policy</code></a> header for details.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"value","title":"Value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>A string; one of the following:</p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"no-referrer\"><code>no-referrer</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Referer\"><code>Referer</code></a> header will be omitted entirely. No referrer\n      information is sent along with requests.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"no-referrer-when-downgrade\"><code>no-referrer-when-downgrade</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      The URL is sent\n      as a referrer when the protocol security level stays the same (e.g.HTTP→HTTP,\n      HTTPS→HTTPS), but isn't sent to a less secure destination (e.g. HTTPS→HTTP).\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"origin\"><code>origin</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Only send the origin of the document as the referrer in all cases.\n      The document <code>https://example.com/page.html</code> will send the referrer\n      <code>https://example.com/</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"origin-when-cross-origin\"><code>origin-when-cross-origin</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Send a full URL when performing a same-origin request, but only send the origin of\n      the document for other cases.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"same-origin\"><code>same-origin</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      A referrer will be sent for <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Same-origin_policy\">same-site origins</a>, but\n      cross-origin requests will contain no referrer information.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"strict-origin\"><code>strict-origin</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Only send the origin of the document as the referrer when the protocol security\n      level stays the same (e.g. HTTPS→HTTPS), but don't send it to a less secure\n      destination (e.g. HTTPS→HTTP).\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\"><code>strict-origin-when-cross-origin</code> (default)</dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      This is the user agent's default behavior if no policy is specified. Send a full URL when performing a same-origin request, only send the origin when the\n      protocol security level stays the same (e.g. HTTPS→HTTPS), and send no header to a\n      less secure destination (e.g. HTTPS→HTTP).\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"unsafe-url\"><code>unsafe-url</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Send a full URL when performing a same-origin or cross-origin request. This policy\n      will leak origins and paths from TLS-protected resources to insecure origins.\n      Carefully consider the impact of this setting.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> links <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> document<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getElementsByTagName</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"link\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nlinks<span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>referrerPolicy<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// \"no-referrer\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/semantics.html#dom-link-referrerpolicy","title":"HTML Standard"}],"query":"api.HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/referrerPolicy/bcd.json"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>HTTP header <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Referrer-Policy\"><code>Referrer-Policy</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLAnchorElement/referrerPolicy\"><code>HTMLAnchorElement.referrerPolicy</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLAreaElement/referrerPolicy\"><code>HTMLAreaElement.referrerPolicy</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLIFrameElement/referrerPolicy\"><code>HTMLIFrameElement.referrerPolicy</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLImageElement/referrerPolicy\"><code>HTMLImageElement.referrerPolicy</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Value","id":"value"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The\n  HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy\n  property reflect the HTML referrerpolicy attribute of the\n  <link> element defining which referrer is sent when fetching the\n  resource.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:14:42.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/htmllinkelement/referrerpolicy","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/htmllinkelement/referrerpolicy/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/277e5969c63b97cfb55ab4a0e612e8040810f49b","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement","title":"HTMLLinkElement"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLLinkElement/referrerPolicy","title":"HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy"}],"pageTitle":"HTMLLinkElement.referrerPolicy - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}